						  <p>
<p>
None of these technologies is perfect and in all County games, Shield games and the other domestic tournaments players have to accept umpires decisions and get on with it. Mistakes by officials occur in every sport and should be seen as part and parcel of what, after all, is a game. Even after five minutes staring at a TV screen it's sometimes difficult to be sure the decision is right. These days we sometimes seem to spend as much time discussing the technology as the cricket itself. Talk about putting the cart before the horse!
</p>	
						  </p>
					   </li>

					   <li>
						  <div>
