<p>
Technically speaking, HotSpot should've been there. It makes complete sense. However, since it costs a lot and it is the broadcasters who have to pay individually, it certainly isn't the most economical cricket technology. Snicko has a major glitch when the sounds cannot be differentiated between. This creates a lot of confusion. Hawkeye can go wrong if the digital pitch map is incorrectly positioned because of the cameras.
</p>	
