<p>
The hawk-eye is the controversial tool, not hotspot. Although if it's due to the high costs and unfeasibility, then it makes sense to not have it - which brings us back to the point of how important it is for the sport to have a *universal* decision reviews system, instead of bits and pieces being used in different series.
