					   <li>
						  <div class="user_comment">
							 <span class="user_name">
	
					<fb:name uid="100007737577387" useyou="false"/></fb:name>
							 
							 <span> 
							 on </span></span>
							 <span class="date">February  7, 2015, 13:28 GMT</span>
						  </div>
						  <p>
<p>
@BAPPCRIC, i agree with your point on the limitations of ball tracking for LBW decisions, but it is still better this technique is used because the main purpose of using these technologies is to take out the bias from the umpires. Umpires can simply give some one out or not out depending upon their own personal reasons but with this technology it is same for everyone. What we want is taking out the human factor as much as possible wherever and whenever possible because the human factor brings the bias, favoritism etc  and we do not want that. Umpires too can make many mistakes. Players career can be spoilt due to umpiring errors - either deliberate or accidental  and by using the technology this bias can be avoided.
</p>	
						  </p>
					   </li>

